<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 is: A project shall not contain unreachable code.

</misra_rule>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- is_rule_violated: whether the rule is violated or not (true/false),
- scenario: a specific violation scenario.
</response format>
<target_code>
Here is the code of UT_ClearDefaultReturnValue:
```c
void UT_ClearDefaultReturnValue(UT_EntryKey_t FuncKey)
{
    UT_StubTableEntry_t *StubPtr;

    StubPtr = UT_GetStubEntry(FuncKey, UT_ENTRYTYPE_RETVAL_CONFIG_CONSTANT);
    if (StubPtr != NULL)
    {
        UT_ClearStubEntry(StubPtr);
    }
}
```
</target_code>
<target_code>
Here is the code fragment that you need to analyze:
```c
void UT_ClearDefaultReturnValue(UT_EntryKey_t FuncKey)
{
    UT_StubTableEntry_t *StubPtr;

    StubPtr = UT_GetStubEntry(FuncKey, UT_ENTRYTYPE_RETVAL_CONFIG_CONSTANT);
    if (StubPtr != NULL)
    {
        UT_ClearStubEntry(StubPtr);
    }
}
```
Focus on the above code fragment and judge whether it violates the rule 2.1 or not.
</target_code>
scenario: No violation: the code contains no unreachable statements. The conditional branch (if (StubPtr != NULL)) is dependent on the runtime return value of UT_GetStubEntry, so both the true and false paths are potentially reachable; there is no dead or unreachable code in this fragment.
